instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin integrates modelling, simulation, monitoring, and optimisation within a single framework. Deployment‑time models are continuously updated via calibration algorithms that refine the physics and cyber models of the cyber‑physical system (CPS) and its environment using real‑time sensor data collected from the physical twin. The calibrated models and synthesized data are then provided to safety and optimality monitors which evaluate operational compliance. When a violation is detected, either human operators or autonomous decision‑making algorithms may intervene to modify the physical twin. This orchestration pattern couples data ingestion, model calibration, monitoring, and control within a unified architecture, emphasizing data‑driven updates and closed‑loop decision support."
]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin life cycle is structured in four main stages: (1) Development and Modeling – engineers construct abstract representations of the physical system, including CAD models for geometry and differential equation‑based dynamic models for physical interactions; (2) Deployment and Integration – the developed models are integrated into the DT framework, making the DT operational alongside the Physical Twin; (3) Data Acquisition and Calibration – sensor data from the PT are continuously collected and used by calibration algorithms to update model parameters and synchronize the cyber‑physical system; (4) Monitoring and Optimization – the calibrated DT runs monitoring algorithms to assess safety and performance, detects violations, and triggers interaction with human operators or supervisory controllers to adjust the Physical Twin. Lifecycle governance involves continuous model refinement and scenario‑based verification but no explicit governance model is detailed in the document."
]
